context_meta.title: I've taken AncestryDNA, 23andMe, and National Geographic genetics tests — here's how to choose one to try
context_meta.summary: I tried DNA tests from 23andMe, Ancestry, and National Geographic to learn about my family's history and my health. The tests vary in terms of what information they provide and how precise they are. I'm often asked which test I'd recommend. My answer boils down to one question: What do you want to get out of the test? From migration patterns, to how much DNA you have in common to a Neaderthal, here's what you can learn from each report. I've sent my spit off for more genetics tests than anyone else I know. The tests analyzed the DNA in my saliva to find out a host of different things about my ancestry and health.
